ional synthesis of scholarship and larger social commitments he has lived this out in many ways at stanford including working on behalf of politically and medically disenfranchised people in india mexico and guatemala on campus he has turned the stanford tradition of the annual dance marathon into a vehicle dedicated to addressing the hiv aids pandemic by engaging not only stanford students but also local communities and corporations raising more than $100000 his exceptional work was recognized by his participation in the clinton global initiative university conference in april english associate professor michele elam described habib as a superb critical thinker whose work is characterized by creative genius and mature insights she holds him up as a model for others saying that he exemplifies exactly the kind of deeply informed pragmatic and caring leadership that the world needs and stanford enables html+ read more ten undergraduates receive deans award for academic accomplishment http news stanford edu news 2011 search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest cisac honors graduate wins george j mitchell scholarship november 18 2011 cisac fsi stanford announcement honors student investigates attitudes towards prenatal care in guatemala july 16 2010 cisac in the news fse grad student rodrigo pizzaro wins tech museum award december 1 2007 fse news cddrl honors student wins rhodes scholarship november 22 2006 cddrl fsi stanford news cisac fellow wins political science dissertation award november 3 2004 cisac news cisac recognizes 10 honors program graduates 4 with award winning theses june 15 2004 cisac news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
